content:
Add a Typeahead Input Element to a FlexCard

Available beginning Winter '22.

From the FlexCards tab, click a version of a FlexCard to open the FlexCard Designer.
From the Build panel, click Inputs, and drag the Typeahead element onto the canvas.
Configure properties common to all Input elements:

In Field Binding, bind the value of the input element to an existing or new data field.

In Field Label, enter the label that appears next to the element.

In Placeholder, enter temporary text that displays inside the input field.

Check Required if the user must enter or select a value for this input element.

Check Read-only to disable the ability to modify the input values.

In Help Text, enter helpful text about the purpose of the input field.

To enter options from which the user can select, click + Add New in the Options section. Configure the following properties:

Label: Enter the visible label for the option.

Value: Enter the value of the option.

Use As a Default Value: Set as the default option.

To configure additional properties available to the element, click + Add New in the Custom Attributes section.

To execute an action when a user interacts with the input element, click + Add Action.

To add conditions that must be met for the element to display, see Add Conditions to a FlexCard Element.

To style your element, click Style to open the Style panel.
